text:
Spending on national security and defense in the 2020 budget is 5.45% of GDP, - the Ministry of Finance

05 Nov 2019, 18:21


In the draft law on state budget-2020, expenditures on national security and defense amount to 245.8 billion UAH or 5.45% of GDP.

This was reported by the press service of the Ministry of Finance of Ukraine.
In particular, it is planned to direct the expenses of the general fund for this function to:

cash security and wages (with accruals) - UAH 141.4 billion (+ UAH 14.4 billion by 2019);
medicines and dressings - 657.8 million UAH (+ 82.8 million UAH by 2019);
food products - 4.84 billion UAH (+ 248.1 million UAH by 2019);
payment of utilities and energy - 4.9 billion UAH (+ 510.7 million UAH by 2019);
creation, purchase, modernization and repair of weapons and military (special) equipment - UAH 35.4 billion (+ UAH 7.8 billion by 2019);
payment of one-time cash assistance in case of death (death), disability or partial disability and other social payments - 6.66 billion UAH (+ 2.44 billion UAH by 2019);
construction (acquisition) of housing - 2.23 billion UAH (+389.8 million UAH by 2019).

Recall, on November 5, officials gathered for an extraordinary meeting, during which, among other things, they approved the draft 2020 budget for a second reading.
Aleksey Goncharuk said that in the budget for 2020 the government is not looking for additional resources to raise taxes, but suggests reducing administrative costs and servicing the government and central executive bodies by an average of 10%.
Goncharuk also called the new figures of the state budget for 2020.

